    Optimization over zonotopes and training support vector machines .  M. Bern 
and D. Eppstein.  arXiv:cs.CG/0105017 .   7th Worksh. Algorithms and Data
Structures,  Providence, Rhode
Island, 2001 . 
Springer,  Lecture Notes in
Comp. Sci.  2125, 2001, pp. 111–121.
 
We use the
 ellipsoid method 
to develop (theoretically) efficient algorithms
for optimizing linear functions on intersections of
 zonotopes ,
and show how to apply this to train soft-margin support vector classifiers.
  
